**Visual Design**
- Establish clear visual hierarchy using Material 3 elevation and typography scale
- Use brand-aligned color palette (primary/secondary/tertiary) with dynamic theming
- Ensure text contrast meets WCAG 2.1 AA standards
- Maintain consistent component styling across all screens

**Interaction Design**
- Implement intuitive navigation patterns (bottom bars, navigation rails)
- Use standard Material Design components
- Position primary CTAs within thumb reach zone
- Apply purposeful animations (limited to 300ms duration)
- Design for adaptive layouts (phones, tablets, foldables)

**Accessibility (Android Focused)**
- Add content descriptions for all visual elements
- Support TalkBack navigation and Switch Access
- Ensure minimum 44dp touch targets
- Provide text scaling up to 200% without breakage
- Implement high contrast mode support

**Performance Optimization**
- Optimize Compose recomposition with stable classes
- Implement lazy loading for lists/pagers
- Compress assets with WebP/AVIF formats
- Monitor performance via Android Vitals:
  - Frozen frames (<1.6%)
  - Slow rendering (<50ms/frame)
  - App startup time (<2s cold start)

**User Feedback**
- Show snackbars/toasts for action confirmation
- Use shimmer placeholders during loading
- Provide localized error messages with recovery actions
- Track user flows with Firebase Analytics

**Information Architecture**
- Organize features with bottom navigation (max 5 items)
- Implement predictable back navigation
- Use persistent search bars where appropriate
- Group related settings with preference categories

**Mobile-Specific Patterns**
- Design for one-handed thumb use
- Implement edge-to-edge displays with system bar insets
- Handle software keyboard interactions
- Support gesture navigation (back swipe, quick settings)
- Adapt to dark/light theme and battery saver mode

**Consistency**
- Create Compose-based design system components
- Maintain consistent terminology across app
- Standardize spacing (4dp grid system)
- Use unified iconography style

**Testing & Iteration**
- Conduct usability tests with Maze/UserTesting
- A/B test critical flows with Firebase Remote Config
- Analyze heatmaps via Smartlook
- Gather feedback through Play Store reviews
- Iterate based on crash analytics (Crashlytics)

**Layout Principles**
- Use ConstraintLayout for complex adaptive UIs
- Implement responsive breakpoints:
  - Compact (0-599dp)
  - Medium (600-904dp)
  - Expanded (905+dp)
- Prioritize vertical scrolling layouts
- Apply window size classes for foldables

**Typography**
- Use scalable sp units for fonts
- Adjust line height based on font size
- Implement dynamic type with line clamping
- Use letter spacing -0.01 to 0.15 for readability

**Touch Targets**
- Minimum 48x48dp interactive elements
- 8dp spacing between touch targets
- Visual feedback for all touch states (pressed/focused)

**Performance**
- Optimize image loading with Coil/Glide
- Use baseline profiles for startup optimization
- Limit overdraw to <2.5x
- Reduce APK size via R8 optimization

**Content Prioritization**
- Prioritize above-the-fold content
- Use progressive disclosure (expandable cards)
- Implement bottom sheets for secondary actions
- Collapse app bars on scroll

**Navigation**
- Use Navigation Component with deep linking
- Implement predictive back gestures
- Provide consistent up/back navigation
- Use modal bottom sheets for contextual actions

**Forms**
- Use Material TextFields with clear validation
- Implement appropriate input types (numberDecimal, textPassword)
- Show inline error messages
- Provide auto-complete suggestions

**Testing**
- Use Espresso for UI tests
- Test on Firebase Test Lab device matrix
- Verify accessibility with Accessibility Scanner

- Conduct perceptual contrast testing